State is similar to props, but it is private and fully controlled by the component ,i.e., it is not accessible to any other component till the owner component decides to pass it.

What are props in React?

Props are inputs to components. They are single values or objects containing a set of values that are passed to components on creation similar to HTML-tag attributes. Here, the data is passed down from a parent component to a child component.The primary purpose of props in React is to provide following component functionality:
Pass custom data to your component.
Trigger state changes.
