First, we should know about tail call before talking about "Proper Tail Call". A tail call is a subroutine or
 function call performed as the final action of a calling function. Whereas Proper tail call(PTC) is a technique
 where the program or code will not create additional stack frames for a recursion when the function call is a tail
 call.For example, the below classic or head recursion of factorial function relies on stack for each step. Each step
 need to be processed upto n * factorial(n - 1)javascript
 function factorial(n) {
   if (n === 0) {
     return 1;
   }
   return n * factorial(n - 1);
 }
 console.log(factorial(5)); //120But if you use Tail recursion functions, they keep passing all the necessary data it needs down the recursion
 without relying on the stack.javascript
 function factorial(n, acc = 1) {
   if (n === 0) {
     return acc;
   }
   return factorial(n - 1, n * acc);
 }
 console.log(factorial(5)); //120The above pattern returns the same output as the first one. But the accumulator keeps track of total as an argument
 without using stack memory on recursive calls.

